Introduction

7SENSES (also known as SEN7ES) is a special sub-unit of the Chinese girl group SNH48. They first debuted in China on March 27, 2017, with the performance of the song "Girl Crush" at the 24th ERC Chinese Top Ten Awards. They released their debut EP SEVEN SEN7ES on April 7, 2017. They debuted in Korea with the digital single "Swan" on February 13, 2019. On March 24, 2021 Bee left the group. On October 31, 2022, SNH48 announced on Weibo that Zhang YuGe (Tako) has officially left SEN7ES, and the group will be continuing as 5.
